theorem frontier_empty_iff_closure_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    frontier (A : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) ↔ (closure A : Set X) = interior A := by
  constructor
  · intro hFrontEmpty
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro x hxCl
      by_cases hxInt : x ∈ interior A
      · exact hxInt
      · have hFront : x ∈ frontier (A : Set X) := And.intro hxCl hxInt
        have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
          simpa [hFrontEmpty] using hFront
        cases this
    · exact interior_subset
  · intro hEq
    have hFrontDef :
        frontier (A : Set X) = closure A \ interior A := by
      simpa using
        (frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A))
    calc
      frontier (A : Set X)
          = closure A \ interior A := hFrontDef
      _ = interior A \ interior A := by
          simpa [hEq]
      _ = (∅ : Set X) := by
          simp [Set.diff_self]

theorem P1_P2_P3_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P1 (Set.univ : Set X) ∧
      Topology.P2 (Set.univ : Set X) ∧
        Topology.P3 (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  exact
    And.intro
      (Topology.P1_univ (X := X))
      (And.intro
        (Topology.P2_univ (X := X))
        (Topology.P3_univ (X := X)))
